message.content: OpenAI is an artificial intelligence research lab that aims to ensure that artificial general intelligence (AGI) benefits all of humanity. AGI refers to highly autonomous systems that can outperform humans in most economically valuable work. OpenAI conducts cutting-edge research, publishes most of its AI work, and also develops AI technologies and applications to address fundamental AI challenges. The organization promotes collaboration and cooperation with other research and policy institutions to create a global community working together to address the global challenges posed by AGI.

message.content: OpenAI was founded in December 2015 by Elon Musk, Sam Altman, Greg Brockman, Ilya Sutskever, Wojciech Zaremba, and John Schulman. Elon Musk, a prominent entrepreneur and CEO of companies like Tesla and SpaceX, was an early supporter of AI safety and co-founded OpenAI with the mission to ensure AGI benefits all of humanity. Sam Altman, a well-known entrepreneur and former president of the startup accelerator Y Combinator, joined forces with Musk to establish OpenAI as a research organization. The other founders are prominent researchers and engineers in the field of artificial intelligence.
